 around zero torque locations, predicted by MHD and\nHD simulations, are needed for the planet to accrete all the available material\naccumulated at the pressure maxima. Pressure maxima generated at the edges of a\nlow-viscosity region of a protoplanetary disk seem to be preferential locations\nfor the formation and trap of massive cores.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Oct 2016 23:18:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Mar 2017 22:49:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-26"}
